id.apigo

Class Apigo

  • java.lang.Object
    • id.apigo.Apigo

  • public final class Apigo
extends Object
    The Apigo class contains static functions that handle global configuration for the Apigo library.

    • Method Detail

      • setLogLevel

        public static void setLogLevel(LogLevel level)
        Sets the level of logging to display, where each level includes all those below it. The default level is LogLevel.NONE. Please ensure this is set to LogLevel.ERROR or LogLevel.NONE before deploying your app to ensure no sensitive information is logged. The levels are:
        • LogLevel.VERBOSE
        • LogLevel.DEBUG
        • LogLevel.INFO
        • LogLevel.WARN
        • LogLevel.ERROR
        • LogLevel.NONE
        Parameters:
        level - The level of logcat logging that Apigo should do.

        Returns:
        The level of logcat logging.

      • initialize

        public static void initialize(Context appContext,
                              String server,
                              String applicationId,
                              String clientKey)
        Authenticates this client as belonging to your application.

        This method is only required if you intend to use a different applicationId

        This must be called before your application can use the Apigo library. The recommended way is to put a call to Apigo.initialize in your Application's onCreate method: 

         public class MyApplication extends Application {
   public void onCreate() {
     super.onCreate();
     Apigo.initialize(this, "SERVER", "APPLICATION_ID", "CLIENT_KEY");
   }
 }
        Parameters:
        appContext - The active application Context for your application.
        server - The server address of Apigo cloud.
        applicationId - The application id provided in the Mesosfer cloud.
        clientKey - The client key provided in the Mesosfer cloud.
